(2, 1, '2013-07-09 01:00:21', '2013-07-09 08:00:21', '<h1>A House of Prayer for All People</h1>\r\nThe Church of the Latter Rain is a non-denominational church where Jesus Christ is the Head and Chief Cornerstone.  We are a diverse fellowship where God is no respector of persons. All are welcome to be inspired by the truth, connect with the Lord on a greater level and experience a life-changing movement.', 'Home', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'home', '', '', '2013-07-14 18:44:53', '2013-07-15 01:44:53', '', 0, 'http://gac.bkc-stage.com/?page_id=2', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(5, 1, '2013-07-09 18:15:40', '2013-07-10 01:15:40', '<p dir="ltr"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-213" alt="our-story" src="http://gac.bkc-stage.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/our-story.jpg" />The Church of the Latter Rain (also known as General Assembly Church) is a bible-based fellowship of churches that believe in the virgin birth, death, resurrection and ascension of Jesus Christ. We strive to be a united family that is focused on helping each other develop a closer walk with the Lord.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">We trace our roots back to the church that Jesus Christ established in the 1st century, which was built on His solid teachings and doctrines that were imparted to the twelve apostles. Following the death of the twelve apostles, false ministers entered the church, and that once powerful church lost its spiritual strength, but not completely. A remnant of people continued to hold fast to the Word of God and persevered through many adversities to preach and practice the doctrines of Christ.</p>\r\nSince that time there have been generations of God-called men and spiritual movements that have led us to this great day. We are a part of this lineage and are working toward the full restoration of God’s church, which will operate in the same perfect order as the Early Rain Church that was established in the 1st century. The restoration of God’s church is imminent and undeniably upon us. The Lord is revealing His truth to those that seek him and illuminating His people so that they can elevate to the next level in his Spirit and love.', 'Our Story', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'about-us', '', '', '2013-07-16 15:39:25', '2013-07-16 22:39:25', '', 0, 'http://gac.bkc-stage.com/?page_id=5', 1, 'page', '', 0),
(22, 1, '2013-07-12 15:51:44', '2013-07-12 22:51:44', '“I had trouble living a balanced life before I came to the church in 1977, but the mercy of the Lord and the kindness of His people is what helped me get my life together. The people didn’t judge me and sincerely wanted the best for me. I never felt that type of love before. When I came into the church I didn’t have much to wear and people would give me clothes. That same love is still here nearly forty years later.\r\n\r\n“I would have never graduated from college, maintained a good job, have any natural achievement and be a productive citizen if it were not for the Lord leading me to His church. When I came to church, I was not familiar with the scriptures; it was like reading a difficult novel and not understanding the plot, but when I heard the Word of God from a man of God it was revolutionary. I began to read the New Testament first and it was amazing. The Book of Acts was an eye-opener. I was blown away to learn about a vision of a church, how it came about, the Holy Ghost being poured out, and people having all things common and willing to go to jail and sacrifice their life for what they believed. That commitment and depth was truly remarkable and is something that I strive for today.”', 'Sister Joyce', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'sister-joyce', '', '', '2013-07-14 20:13:03', '2013-07-15 03:13:03', '', 0, 'http://gac.bkc-stage.com/?post_type=members&#038;p=22', 0, 'members', '', 0),
