(50, 1, '2013-07-14 09:35:16', '2013-07-14 16:35:16', 'Brother Lacy Hawkins began serving the Lord in 1960 and launched the Church of the Latter Rain as General Assembly Church in 1974 in Berkeley, California.  In the 1980s, his ministry expanded to Solano County and he built the Church at Vallejo in 1986 and added a state-of-the-art gymnasium and football field in 1992 for youth to have a safe environment for recreational activities.  He went on to establish three more churches in Union City, California (1994), Baton Rouge, Louisiana (2000), Moreno Valley, California (2001) and Tyler, Texas (2003). In 2012, the Church at Burbank, the Church at Livingston and the Church at Clarksville began to join the Church of the Latter Rain fellowship.\r\n\r\nBrother Hawkins was called to the ministry in 1963 and has labored forty years to build the churches into Jesus Christ, preaching God’s perfect order, unity and divine love.  He has taken many stands for righteousness to ensure that all people have an opportunity to receive the truth of the Word of God and he continues to preach in all of the Church of the Latter Rain assemblies helping many people to establish stable “natural and spiritual” lives.', 'Lacy Hawkins', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'lacy-hawkins', '', '', '2013-07-16 21:53:29', '2013-07-17 04:53:29', '', 0, 'http://gac.bkc-stage.com/?post_type=ministers&#038;p=50', 0, 'ministers', '', 0),
