(71, 1, '2013-07-14 18:21:46', '2013-07-15 01:21:46', 'Brother Darrell Booker is the lead minister for the Church at Vallejo. He began his walk with the Lord in 1977 and received the Holy Ghost shortly thereafter. He was converted at a Monday night prayer meeting and from that moment forward, the Lord began to change his life and gave him an appetite to read the Word of God. By reading the Word of God, his heart began to transform and his interests were focused on what he could do to help the people of God just as they helped him when he was a new convert.\r\n\r\nBrother Darrell has dedicated his life to serving and encouraging the people of the Lord. He was ordained a minister in 1993 and is passionate about strengthening families and those in need.\r\n\r\nBrother Darrell Booker works closely with other ministers to support the church, including: Brother Ray Anderson, Brother Rick Bordeau, Brother Tyrone Duffel, Brother Caesar English, Brother Frank Hethcock, Brother Darryl Johnson, Brother Jose Vega, Brother Greg Nickelson, Brother Roger Bell and Brother Victor Arias.\r\n\r\nHe is married to Cecelia, his wife of nearly 35 years.', 'Darrell Booker', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'darrell-booker', '', '', '2013-07-16 22:22:34', '2013-07-17 05:22:34', '', 0, 'http://gac.bkc-stage.com/?post_type=ministers&#038;p=71', 2, 'ministers', '', 0),
