(85, 1, '2013-07-14 18:54:59', '2013-07-15 01:54:59', 'Brother Darral Brown is the lead minister for the Church at Baton Rouge. He came in contact with the church through a co-worker in 1984 at the age of 19 while in the Air Force stationed at Misawa, Japan. It was through listening to audio recordings of church services he received from his co-worker during his three year tour in Japan that he was converted by the preaching of the word or God. Although he hadn’t met Brother Lacy Hawkins, nor visited the church, he was captivated by his teaching of the Doctrines of Christ and this foundation sustained him until he was able to visit the Church of the Latter Rain for the first time in 1991. During his first visit, he was water baptized and received the baptism of the Holy Ghost and began his life changing journey with the Lord.\r\n\r\nHe was stationed in Georgia at the time, but through a miraculous chain of events received a transfer to Travis Air Force Base in Fairfield, California in 1995 which brought him to the Vallejo assembly. Finally, he was able to attend worship services after eleven years of audio and video recordings. When it was time for him to transfer to a different location due to his official Air Force obligations, he prayed for an assignment near a Church of the Latter Rain assembly. The Lord granted his request and moved him and his family to Baton Rouge in 2000, which was a new church at the time. That same year Brother Darral was ordained a minister in Baton Rouge and shortly thereafter became the lead minister. He works closely with other ministers to support the church, including: Brother David Lemmons, Brother Wayne Reed and Brother Stan Wooden.\r\n\r\nHe continues to support and encourage the people of God in their salvation. He has been married to his high school sweetheart, Alisa for nearly 30 years.', 'Darral Brown', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'darral-brown', '', '', '2013-07-16 21:56:28', '2013-07-17 04:56:28', '', 0, 'http://gac.bkc-stage.com/?post_type=ministers&#038;p=85', 3, 'ministers', '', 0),
(88, 1, '2013-07-14 18:59:20', '2013-07-15 01:59:20', 'Brother Tim Drennen is the lead minister for the Church at Moreno Valley. He was converted to the Lord in 1984 and came to the Church at Vallejo in 1986 after the Lord led him from North Carolina. After praying for many years for the Lord to show him he was real, Brother Tim received his answer when he heard Brother Lacy Hawkins minister for the first time and when he saw young people speaking in other tongues. Shortly after coming to the church, Brother Tim was singing a song during a church service when the Spirit of God fell on him and he was filled with the Holy Ghost.\r\n\r\nOver the years, Brother Tim worked on many church teams such as dishwashing, sanctuary clean up, security and maintenance where he used his construction skills to help build the Vallejo church. He was ordained a minister in 2003 and moved to Albuquerque, New Mexico and supported the work there until the church was closed. In 2010, he and his wife of 34 years, Laurie moved to Moreno Valley where he now supports the growth and development of this assembly. He works closely with other ministers to support the church, including: Brother Robert Bean and Brother David Hesterly.', 'Tim Drennen', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'tim-drennen', '', '', '2013-07-16 21:57:04', '2013-07-17 04:57:04', '', 0, 'http://gac.bkc-stage.com/?post_type=ministers&#038;p=88', 4, 'ministers', '', 0),
(92, 1, '2013-07-14 19:01:26', '2013-07-15 02:01:26', 'Brother Vern Kelley is the lead minister for the Church at Union City. He first came in contact with the Church of the Latter Rain in 1975 when he noticed a change in the lives of his college friends who were attending the church. A personal experience caused him to wonder what happens to a man when he dies, and that led him to accept his friends’ invitations to visit the church in Berkeley. He began to seek the same joy and peace they had received. After a few visits he was convinced the church was the place he should worship. He received the baptism of the Holy Ghost in 1977 when he called on the name of Jesus meaningfully and with all his might.\r\n\r\nBrother Vern has been a faithful member of the church, volunteering on various church teams including dishwashing, maintenance, church clean up and ushers. He was ordained a minister in 1984 and works closely with other ministers to support the church, including: Brother Charles Buffin, Brother Harry Carthan, Brother Rodger Cooper, Brother LJ Douglas, Brother Clyde Hawkins, Brother Lawrence James, Brother Earl Johnson and Brother Etienne Johnson.\r\n\r\nHe has been married to his college sweetheart, Erma for 35 years.', 'Vern Kelley', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'vern-kelley', '', '', '2013-07-16 21:57:33', '2013-07-17 04:57:33', '', 0, 'http://gac.bkc-stage.com/?post_type=ministers&#038;p=92', 5, 'ministers', '', 0),
(95, 1, '2013-07-14 19:02:43', '2013-07-15 02:02:43', 'Brother Brian Wallace is the lead minister for the Church at Tyler. He first came in contact with the Lord as a young boy and began to seek more of God through youth groups, Christian music, and even experienced several missionary trips. As a teenager he began to question whether or not he knew Jesus well enough to tell others about His saving grace. Throughout his formative years he attended many different churches, but couldn’t find the balance and stability he desired.\r\n\r\nAt the age of 18 years old, Brother Brian received the baptism of the Holy Ghost at a small church that he was attending. Shortly thereafter, he came in contact with the Church of the Latter Rain and heard things that he had never heard before, such as a minister encouraging people to read and study the bible for themselves. He began to read the Word of God and it gave him the stability he was looking for and the power to change. Brother Brian has attended the church since 1986 and was ordained a minister in 2003. He works closely with other ministers to support the church, including: Brother Al Chatman and Brother Jerry Stine.\r\n\r\nHe is married to LaShun, his wife of 23 years.', 'Brian Wallace', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'brian-wallace', '', '', '2013-07-16 21:58:06', '2013-07-17 04:58:06', '', 0, 'http://gac.bkc-stage.com/?post_type=ministers&#038;p=95', 6, 'ministers', '', 0),
