(130, 1, '2013-07-14 20:56:46', '2013-07-15 03:56:46', '“The first thing that impressed me about the church was the love and care the people showed me and my family without asking anything in return. When my family moved here from Minnesota, I was trying to enroll my daughters in daycare, but the daycare only had room for one of them. Another mother from the church heard about my situation and gave up her child’s spot so that my girls could be in daycare together. Without saying what you need, the people give of themselves.\r\n\r\n“My girls are older now and the principles that I’ve learned at the church coupled with the Word of God has helped my husband and I raise well-rounded, friendly, success-minded young girls. I would not have known how to do that without the Lord and the help of His people. My youngest daughter was valedictorian of her middle school and my oldest daughter is ranked in the upper percentile of her high school class. Teachers have commended us as parents for raising a young daughter who is conscientious and actively learning. Everything I learned about parenting, I’ve learned here.”', 'Sister Adrienne', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'sister-adrienne', '', '', '2013-07-14 20:56:46', '2013-07-15 03:56:46', '', 0, 'http://gac.bkc-stage.com/?post_type=members&#038;p=130', 2, 'members', '', 0),
