(184, 1, '2013-07-15 14:04:46', '2013-07-15 21:04:46', 'The Church at Baton Rouge first opened its doors in 1996. In 2000, a new building was constructed on Staring Lane for everyone to worship the Lord, and where God is no respector of persons.\r\n\r\nThis church has a diverse congregation of people of all ages and walks of life. Each year during October, the church hosts a National Convention where all Church of the Latter Rain assemblies come together for several days to worship the Lord and fellowship each other.', 'Church at Baton Rouge', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'church-at-baton-rouge', '', '', '2013-07-16 08:15:17', '2013-07-16 15:15:17', '', 0, 'http://gac.bkc-stage.com/?post_type=churches&#038;p=184', 0, 'churches', '', 0),
(186, 1, '2013-07-15 14:06:06', '2013-07-15 21:06:06', 'In the heart of the Inland Empire is the Church at Moreno Valley, which first launched in 2001 at a small building off Alessandro Street. In 2005, the Lord blessed the church to build a new facility on Pigeon Pass Road, where members joyfully serve the Lord in Spirit and in truth.\r\n\r\nThe Church at Moreno Valley frequently hosts regional fellowships in May where the churches in Northern California come together for two powerful days of spirit and truth. The church also supports a smaller assembly in Burbank.', 'Church at Moreno Valley', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'church-at-moreno-valley', '', '', '2013-07-16 21:59:18', '2013-07-17 04:59:18', '', 0, 'http://gac.bkc-stage.com/?post_type=churches&#038;p=186', 1, 'churches', '', 0),
(188, 1, '2013-07-15 14:07:07', '2013-07-15 21:07:07', 'The Church at Tyler is situated in a charming community of East Texas. The church opened its doors in 2003. A gymnasium for educational and recreational activities is also a part of the property. The Tyler church is a tight-knit group who actively support each other in serving the Lord.', 'Church at Tyler', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'church-at-tyler', '', '', '2013-07-15 14:45:35', '2013-07-15 21:45:35', '', 0, 'http://gac.bkc-stage.com/?post_type=churches&#038;p=188', 2, 'churches', '', 0),
(190, 1, '2013-07-15 14:08:19', '2013-07-15 21:08:19', 'The Church at Union City is nestled among the business- lined streets of an industrial neighborhood. Since 1994, the Church at Union City has been a house of prayer for all God\'s people. The facility accommodates a sizable congregation and includes an Education and Recreation center with a gymnasium and football field.\r\n\r\nEach summer, the Church at Union City hosts a National Convention filling the sanctuary with members and visitors from across the United States.', 'Church at Union City', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'church-at-union-city', '', '', '2013-07-16 08:14:54', '2013-07-16 15:14:54', '', 0, 'http://gac.bkc-stage.com/?post_type=churches&#038;p=190', 3, 'churches', '', 0),
(192, 1, '2013-07-15 14:09:14', '2013-07-15 21:09:14', 'The Church at Vallejo was established in 1981 as the first branch assembly in Northern California. For more than three decades, the Church at Vallejo has been a pillar in the Bay Area with congregants traveling from several local counties to assemble in the house of God. The church was built in 1986 and its Education and Recreation center was built in 1992, and continues to be a refuge for many youth.\r\n\r\nEven though the Church at Vallejo is the largest assembly in the Church of the Latter Rain fellowship, you will find a family of God that is fitly joined together and compacted in love. The Vallejo church also supports the Church at Clarksville in Indiana.', 'The Church at Vallejo', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-church-at-vallejo', '', '', '2013-07-15 14:46:29', '2013-07-15 21:46:29', '', 0, 'http://gac.bkc-stage.com/?post_type=churches&#038;p=192', 4, 'churches', '', 0),
